

Exercise:
2026-01-31 - Traffic Analysis Exercise: Lumma in the Room-Ah

Background:
This exercise is based on a Security Operations Center (SOC) scenario where an alert was triggered for ET MALWARE Lumma Stealer Victim Fingerprinting Activity from IP address 153.92.1.49 over TCP port 80.

The alert was triggered on:
2026-01-27 at 23:05 UTC

Environment Details:
- LAN range: 10.1.21.0/24
- Domain: win11office.com
- Active Directory: WIN11OFFICE
- Domain Controller: 10.1.21.2 (WIN-LU4L24X3UB7)
- Gateway: 10.1.21.1

Task:
The goal of this exercise is to analyze the PCAP file and answer the following:

- What is the IP address of the infected Windows client?
- What is the MAC address of the infected Windows client?
- What is the host name of the infected Windows client?
- What is the user account name from the infected Windows client?
- What is the full name of the user from the user account?
- What is the domain from 153.92.1.49 that triggered the alert?

